! Examples

!! Example: drop a meeting invite

After dropping `kickoff.msg` into a `<$file-dropzone>`, the resulting `kickoff.msg.email` tiddler looks roughly like:

```
---
type: text/x-frontmattered-markdown
msg-subject: "Project Apollo kickoff"
msg-from: "Alice Smith <alice@example.com>"
msg-to:
  - bob@example.com
  - carol@example.com
msg-cc: []
msg-bcc: []
msg-date: 2026-05-13T08:42:00+00:00
msg-message-id: <CAJq8...@mail.example.com>
msg-in-reply-to: ""
msg-has-attachments: yes
tags: email
---

# Project Apollo kickoff

Hi all,

Let's get the kickoff scheduled for next Tuesday. See the attached agenda...

![](/files/email/_derived/kickoff.msg/cid_logo123.png)
```

The agenda PDF lives at `kickoff.msg.attachments/att_agenda.pdf` with `_artifact_source = kickoff.msg`.

!! Example: enable the LLM summary step

```
<$action-setfield $tiddler="$:/config/rimir/msg-import/llm-summary" text="yes"/>
```

Re-drop a message. A new `kickoff.msg.summary` tiddler appears with the LLM-produced digest (TL;DR + decisions + action items + open questions, per `prompts/email-summary.tid`).

!! Example: override the LLM provider per dropzone

```
<$file-dropzone pipeline="auto"
  prop-system-prompt="$:/my/custom-system-prompt"
  prop-provider="anthropic"
  prop-model="claude-opus-4-7"/>
```

The three `prop-*` attributes are passed through file-pipeline's client to the LLM step. They take precedence over llm-connect's global defaults but lose to step-level fields set in the pipeline tiddler.
